SYNOPSIS
	void set_auto_load(int iArg)

DEFINED IN
	ob.c

DESCRIPTION
	Sets the bit_flag on an object to '<iArg>' showing it as either an
	auto_load object or not.

	NOTE: This flag is automatically set on an object that is created
	      from a players autoload list when they login. It is also set
	      on an object that is passed to the function 'register_auto_obj'

EXAMPLE
	// This example flags the object as an auto_load object
	object oObj = clone("/objects/hat");
	oObj->set_auto_load(1);

SEE ALSO
	register_auto_obj, remove_auto_obj, query_auto_obj, query_auto_load
